  "title": "Aureline customer-managed-key and storage selection flows, region/residency cues, and degraded managed-service continuity",
  "description": "Export-safe packet for the residency and offboarding depth lane: the key custody selection flow that records which key-custody options (customer-managed-key, provider-managed-key, local-only-no-escrow) are offered and which is active, the storage selection flow that records which storage locations are offered and which is active, the region/residency cues that disclose where each managed artifact scope resides and whether the residency pin is verified, and the managed-service continuity rows that record, per managed-service capability, what stays local and what requires provider or admin continuity when the managed service degrades. It projects four sections — key_custody_selection, storage_selection, residency_cue, and managed_service_continuity; the first three inherit qualification from the frozen M5 companion-matrix residency_encryption lane and managed_service_continuity inherits from the offboarding_continuity lane, and every item carries an exact desktop handoff. Read-only selection with the local core authoritative: every section is read-only, the surface only projects a selection (a key-custody, storage-location, or residency change is applied by the local core, never authored from this surface), and a local-only key option and a local-first storage option are always offered as a fallback. Provable where claimed: a key-custody option claims a verified encryption posture, and a residency cue claims a verified region pin, only when verifiable; an unverifiable claim narrows (claimed_unverified, pinned_unverified) and is labeled rather than shown as proven. Local-first continuity: every continuity row records what stays local and what requires provider or admin continuity, and asserts local_work_preserved so offboarding or a degraded managed service never strands user-owned local work. Degraded state (key management unavailable, storage provider unavailable, stale proof, residency unverified, encryption unverified, admin continuity unavailable, managed service degraded, inactive host, narrowed upstream lane, unresolved handoff, downgraded freshness, selection narrowed to local fallback, downgraded residency claim, downgraded encryption claim) is labeled rather than hidden. Credential bodies, raw key material, raw provider payloads, and raw storage record contents never cross this boundary.",
